Subject: [PATCH 1390/2066] mmc: sh_mobile_sdhi: Fix sampling clock position
 selecting

When the result of CMD19 was different between the first set and
the second set, there was a case where the wrong sampling clock
position was selected.
As a countermeasure, make the two results the same.

Signed-off-by: Masaharu Hayakawa <masaharu.hayakawa.ry@renesas.com>
[zou:Original patch taken from
git://git.kernel.org/pub/scm/linux/kernel/git/horms/renesas-bsp.git
 v4.9/rcar-3.5.1]
Signed-off-by: zou cao <cao.zou@windriver.com>
---
 drivers/mmc/host/sh_mobile_sdhi.c |    9 +++++++++
 1 files changed, 9 insertions(+), 0 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/mmc/host/sh_mobile_sdhi.c b/drivers/mmc/host/sh_mobile_sdhi.c
index dce64ca..5b51598 100644
--- a/drivers/mmc/host/sh_mobile_sdhi.c
+++ b/drivers/mmc/host/sh_mobile_sdhi.c
@@ -419,6 +419,15 @@ static int sh_mobile_sdhi_select_tuning(struct tmio_mmc_host *host)
 	/* Clear SCC_RVSREQ */
 	sd_scc_write32(host, priv, SH_MOBILE_SDHI_SCC_RVSREQ, 0);
 
+	/* Merge the results */
+	for (i = 0; i < host->tap_num * 2; i++) {
+		if (!test_bit(i, host->taps)) {
+			clear_bit(i % host->tap_num, host->taps);
+			clear_bit((i % host->tap_num) + host->tap_num,
+					host->taps);
+		}
+	}
+
